<definition-item><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">F42C7/12</classification-symbol><definition-title>Percussion fuzes of the double-action type, i.e. fuzes cocked and fired in a single movement, e.g. by pulling an incorporated percussion pin or hammer  (percussion caps <class-ref scheme="cpc">F42C19/10</class-ref>)</definition-title><definition-statement>
