<definition-item><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">F42C9/00</classification-symbol><definition-title>Time fuzes; Combined time and percussion or pressure-actuated fuzes; Fuzes for timed self-destruction of ammunition</definition-title><definition-statement>
         <section-title>Definition statement</section-title>
         <section-body>
            <paragraph-text type="preamble">This place covers:</paragraph-text>
            <paragraph-text type="body">Non-electronic fuzes causing detonation of the ammunition after a predetermined time from the initiation of the fuze itself, i.e. the timing is not caused by an electric or electronic circuitry.</paragraph-text>
            <paragraph-text type="body">Timing can be caused by clockwork or a burning pyrotechnic unit.</paragraph-text>
         </section-body>
      </definition-statement><references><section-title>References</section-title><limiting-references>
